sources.title: F.B.I. Girl (1951) Film-Noir Directed by William Berke - Fingerprint Trap: Bureau Secrets Chase!
sources.description:
Shirley Wayne (Audrey Totter) a quick-witted clerk in the fingerprint division, helps G-men nab a shady governor and his accomplice, leading to a high-stakes chase in the name of justice.

Colorized version: https://youtu.be/jbkLzYnZpR0

Director: William Berke
Writers: Dwight V. Babcock, Richard H. Landau, Rupert Hughes
Actors: Audrey Totter, Cesar Romero, George Brent, Raymond Burr

Genres: Crime, Drama, Film-Noir, Thriller
Release date: November 2, 1951
Filming location: Los Angeles

metadata.Plot: A governor planning to run for U.S. Senate has a secret past that could prove damaging to his political aspirations: he's a convicted murderer, and that will come to light if the FBI does an investigative check on him. He goes to a local crime boss for help. The racketeer arranges for a low-level FBI employee to take the incriminating file from FBI headquarters, but then she is conveniently murdered. Two FBI agents investigating her murder begin to think that something isn't quite kosher.
metadata.Writer: Dwight V. Babcock, Richard H. Landau, Rupert Hughes
metadata.Actors: Cesar Romero, George Brent, Audrey Totter
